(282, 'Introduction', 'Python', '<p><strong>What is Python?</strong></p><ul><li>Python is a powerful multiparadigm computer programming language, optimized for programmer productivity, code readability, and software quality.</li></ul><p><strong>Why Python is so popular?</strong></p><ol><li>It is relatively easy to learn.</li><li>It is relatively easy to use.</li><li>It is Object Oriented and functional.</li><li>It is free, portable and powerful.</li><li>It is compatible with other programming languages.</li></ol><p><strong>What can I do with Python?</strong></p><ol><li>Building system level programs.</li><li>GUI application design.</li><li>Web Development.</li><li>Data Science</li><li>Data Analytics</li><li>Machine Learning and AI based models.</li><li>Rapid Prototyping.</li></ol>', 'White (normal card)', 'Click on the Submit and then next to go to the next lesson.', '', '1'),
(283, 'Conceptual Hierarchy', 'Python', '<p>Python programs can be decomposed into modules, statements, expressions, and objects, as follows:</p><ol><li><strong>Programs</strong> are composed of<strong> modules</strong>.</li><li><strong>Modules</strong> contain <strong>statements</strong>.</li><li><strong>Statements</strong> contain <strong>expressions</strong>.</li><li><strong>Expressions</strong> create and process <strong>objects</strong>.</li></ol>', 'White (normal card)', 'Click on the Submit and then next to go to the next lesson.', '', '1');
