(1810, 'About Statistics', 'Python', '<p>Statistics is one of the oldest branches of Mathematics and is used in almost all the industries today. You can find some interesting facts about Statistics along with its historical timeline here.</p><p><strong>What is Statistics?</strong><br>The science of collecting, analyzing, presenting, and interpreting data.</p><p><strong>Why Statistics is important?</strong><br>1. Helps one to use the proper methods to collect the data.<br>2. Helps one employ the correct analysis methodology to the collected data.<br>3. Helps one effectively present the results obtained through analysis.<br>4. Helps one to make informed decisions.<br>5. Helps to present the existing data more effectively.</p><p>There are two types of philosophies in Statistics<br>1. Bayesian statistics<br>2. Frequentist statistics</p><p><br><strong>Note:</strong></p><p>Before getting into the statistics, one has to get a good grasp over many statistical concepts.</p><p>In this course all of them would be exhaustively covered along with relevant theory and exercises.</p><p>Further, it is assumed that the learner has completed basic Python module as this course will be focusing on learning Statistics with Python and not on learning Python.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Click on the Submit and then next to go to the next lesson.', '', '11'),
(1811, 'Bayesian statistics', 'Python', '<p>&nbsp;<br><strong>What is Bayesian statistics?</strong></p><p>It is an approach, which describes the probability of an event occurrence based on previous knowledge of the conditions associated with this event.</p><p>Quite flexible as compared to its counter part.</p><p>Let&#x27;s try to understand this better with an example.</p><p>Let us say a man (who is a famous trickster) rolls a six sided die and it has outcomes 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, or 6.</p><p>Furthermore, he says that if it lands on a 3, he&#x27;ll give you a free amazon voucher.</p><p>The<strong> Bayesian statistician</strong> will calculate the probability of getting a 3 based on the person being a trickster (previous knowledge).</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Click on the Submit and then next to go to the next lesson.', '', '11'),
(1812, 'Frequentist statistics', 'Python', '<p><br><strong>What is Frequentist statistics?</strong></p><p>It is an approach, which makes predictions based on rigid pre-defined mathematical frameworks such as <strong>p-value, confidence interval, hypothesis testing</strong> etc.</p><p>It makes predictions based on the data and frequencies. It is considered to be a more stricter approach.</p><p>In this course we will be focusing more on this approach.</p><p>Let&#x27;s try to understand this better with an example.</p><p>Let us say a man rolls a six sided die and it has outcomes 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, or 6.</p><p>Furthermore, he says that if it lands on a 3, he&#x27;ll give you a free<strong> subscription to this platform.</strong></p><p><strong>Then informally:</strong></p><p>The <strong>Frequentist</strong> would say that each outcome has an equal 1 in 6 chance of occurring.</p><p>It must be mentioned that there is nothing stopping the frequentist to include the prior knowledge but the mathematical framework is followed.<br>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '11');
